		<quantitativeReference type="Reference flow(s)">
			<functionalUnitOrOther xml:lang="en">In this paper, a 1 kWp solar PV system consisting of five 200 Wmodules made of 54 multi-Si cells, each with a size of 156*156 mm2 and 16% efficiency, was used as the primary study object</functionalUnitOrOther>
			<referenceToReferenceFlow>3</referenceToReferenceFlow>
		</quantitativeReference>
		<time>
			<common:referenceYear>2017</common:referenceYear>
			<common:timeRepresentativenessDescription xml:lang="en">Available online</common:timeRepresentativenessDescription>
			<common:timeRepresentativenessDescription xml:lang="zh">文章发表</common:timeRepresentativenessDescription>
		</time>
		<geography>
			<locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction location="CN">
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="en">Environmental effects of China's solar photovoltaic industry during2011e2016: A life cycle assessment approach</descriptionOfRestrictions>
				<descriptionOfRestrictions xml:lang="zh">2011-2016年中国太阳能光伏产业生命周期环境影响评价</descriptionOfRestrictions>
			</locationOfOperationSupplyOrProduction>
		</geography>
		<technology>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="en">Small down-the-hole drill and explosives are used to take apart the source containing the desired deposits by themultiple-row delay blasting technique</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses xml:lang="zh">利用小型井下钻机和炸药，采用多排延时爆破技术，对含有所需矿床的矿源进行分离</technologyDescriptionAndIncludedProcesses>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="en">The described process is utilized in the extraction of silicon ore through the multiple-row delay blasting technique. This technique is part of the production chain for multi-crystalline silicon (Multi-Si) used predominantly in the manufacturing of solar photovoltaic (PV) systems. Specifically, a 1 kWp solar PV system composed of five 200 W modules, each made from 54 Multi-Si cells sized 156*156 mm2 with 16% efficiency, serves as the primary research subject for life cycle assessment studies within the Chinese solar PV industry, representing the application of silicon obtained from this mining process.</technologicalApplicability>
			<technologicalApplicability xml:lang="zh">所描述的工艺用于通过多排延时爆破技术提取硅矿。这种技术是多晶硅生产链的一部分，主要用于制造太阳能光伏系统。具体来说，一个由五个200瓦模块组成的1千瓦峰值太阳能光伏系统，每个模块由54个尺寸为156*156毫米2、效率为16%的多晶硅电池组成，是中国太阳能光伏行业生命周期评估研究的主要研究对象，代表从这个采矿过程中获得的硅的应用。</technologicalApplicability>
			<referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture type="source data set" refObjectId="12a1e0b7-2f33-c1ae-b57b-afe1edf94591" uri="../sources/12a1e0b7-2f33-c1ae-b57b-afe1edf94591.xml">
				<common:shortDescription xml:lang="en">HeFQb9vQhoUnJrxXVTYc6X02nWf.png</common:shortDescription>
			</referenceToTechnologyFlowDiagrammOrPicture>
		</technology>
	</processInformation>
